    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-27T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="886"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/2405: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-27T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >January 27, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 27—11:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. Department’s 55, January 25, 3 p.m., which we have repeated to Shanghai.
                    Wounding of presiding officer of Shanghai Municipal Council.</p>
                <pb facs="0834" n="824" xml:id="pg_824"/>
                <p>In an interview today with the Minister for Foreign Affairs I made informal
                    comment on the incident as authorized by the Department. The Minister said that
                    he was angry and ashamed at the incident, that the Japanese Consul General in
                        Shanghai<note n="76" xml:id="d886fn1">T. Horiuchi.</note> ought never to
                    have allowed the position of the representative of the Japanese Rate Payers to
                    be held by such an irresponsible and [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] individual who
                    is believed to control houses of prostitution in Shanghai, and that drastic
                    action under Japanese law will be taken against the assailant.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department via Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
